WEBVTT

00:08.000 --> 00:10.000
[pulsing music playing]

00:27.833 --> 00:29.916
♪ ♪

00:49.375 --> 00:50.374
[male newscaster] <i>Breaking news,</i>

00:50.375 --> 00:52.707
<i>reports are coming in
from all over the city</i>

00:52.708 --> 00:54.790
<i>of widespread destruction.</i>

00:54.791 --> 00:56.707
[female newscaster] <i>It appears
that Thomas Light's robotic</i>

00:56.708 --> 00:58.249
<i>reinforcements have failed to stop</i>

00:58.250 --> 01:00.332
<i>- his own rampaging machines.</i>
- [Dr. Light gasps]

01:00.333 --> 01:03.124
This doesn't make any sense, Rock.

01:03.125 --> 01:05.124
Wily's turned Metal Man.

01:05.125 --> 01:07.624
I swore the safety protocols, but--

01:07.625 --> 01:08.750
Oh, never mind.

01:08.875 --> 01:10.207
We have to try something else.

01:10.208 --> 01:11.749
I'm ready. How can I help?

01:11.750 --> 01:14.666
[sighs] Open Bay Six.

01:20.750 --> 01:23.791
[soaring music playing]

01:28.416 --> 01:30.040
Bomb Man? Dr. Light...

01:30.041 --> 01:33.583
I know. But he's powerful enough
to stop the others.

01:39.208 --> 01:41.332
Powerful enough to save Mega City.

01:41.333 --> 01:44.457
Maybe this will shield him
from outside signals,

01:44.458 --> 01:48.374
keep Wily from infecting
his cognitive circuit, like the others.

01:48.375 --> 01:49.457
It'll work.

01:49.458 --> 01:51.207
He's our last line of defense.

01:51.208 --> 01:52.957
Maybe not the last.

01:52.958 --> 01:54.415
I could fight.

01:54.416 --> 01:55.540
Y-You could what?

01:55.541 --> 01:57.208
I can go out there and fight them.

01:59.500 --> 02:00.665
Rock.

02:00.666 --> 02:02.665
- I made you because I needed--
- Help!

02:02.666 --> 02:05.040
You made me to help.

02:05.041 --> 02:08.124
- Let me help.
- In the lab, Rock.

02:08.125 --> 02:09.957
Not out there. I mean,

02:09.958 --> 02:12.415
against something this size?

02:12.416 --> 02:15.666
[scoffs] I'm not letting you
throw your life away.

02:23.833 --> 02:26.000
[quiet clinking nearby]

02:30.708 --> 02:32.458
- [garbled chittering]
- Dr. Light!

02:34.250 --> 02:35.415
Dr. Light!

02:35.416 --> 02:37.583
[grunts] Hey, look out!

02:38.833 --> 02:40.582
- Yah!
- Wh--

02:40.583 --> 02:44.250
He's one of Wily's and it's going
for the cerebral controllers.

02:50.083 --> 02:51.082
[both groan]

02:51.083 --> 02:52.457
Ah!

02:52.458 --> 02:54.249
[Rock grunting]

02:54.250 --> 02:56.125
[device beeping]

02:58.041 --> 03:00.541
[groans, grunts]

03:02.458 --> 03:03.707
[beeping]

03:03.708 --> 03:04.874
Run, Rock!

03:04.875 --> 03:06.333
Run!

03:14.333 --> 03:15.833
[exclaims]

03:19.708 --> 03:20.708
Sorry.

03:28.833 --> 03:31.333
- [grunts] Rock!
- [clangs]

03:34.875 --> 03:35.875
No!

03:40.750 --> 03:42.375
Dr. Light!

03:43.916 --> 03:45.374
[grunts] I'm sorry...

03:45.375 --> 03:46.624
[Dr. Light groaning]

03:46.625 --> 03:48.750
I'm here, Rock.

03:50.041 --> 03:52.499
- Are you okay, Doc?
- Yeah.

03:52.500 --> 03:54.125
I'm sorry. Doc...

03:55.125 --> 03:56.083
I'm s--

03:57.333 --> 03:59.415
- [Rock screams]
- Oh!

03:59.416 --> 04:00.666
Rock!

04:12.125 --> 04:13.416
[shouts]

04:15.291 --> 04:17.291
[panting]

04:19.541 --> 04:21.540
I'm sorry.

04:21.541 --> 04:23.165
I'm so sorry.

04:23.166 --> 04:25.540
- No.
- You tried to tell me,

04:25.541 --> 04:27.124
- I wasn't--
- Stop.

04:27.125 --> 04:28.916
Rock...

04:30.375 --> 04:31.790
[exhales]

04:31.791 --> 04:35.666
What you just did was amazing.

04:37.416 --> 04:39.124
I was wrong.

04:39.125 --> 04:41.750
It doesn't matter what I made you for.

04:43.041 --> 04:46.000
This is what you were meant for.

04:47.458 --> 04:49.458
[hopeful music playing]

04:54.208 --> 04:57.041
[intense music playing]

05:08.041 --> 05:09.333
[triumphant grunt]

05:16.875 --> 05:18.040
[Dr. Light] Hey.

05:18.041 --> 05:19.333
Kid.

05:26.875 --> 05:28.875
♪ ♪

05:32.916 --> 05:34.916
[intense music playing]

06:04.583 --> 06:06.583
♪ ♪

06:36.666 --> 06:38.666
♪ ♪
